wiki.text:
'BRB' stands for:
* "Be right back", , also sometimes treated as a synonym of "bathroom break"
*
* Buckling-Restrained Braced Frame, a specialized earthquake bracing system. See
  BRBF and Buckling Restrained Brace
* Bank of the Republic of Burundi or Banque de la République du Burundi, the
  official name in French of the central bank of Burundi
* Bayerische Regiobahn, a train company in Bavaria, Germany
* Benefits Review Board, a part of the United States Department of Labor
* Bibliothèque royale de Belgique, the Royal Library of Belgium
* Big red button, a type of command button
* Birmingham Royal Ballet, a ballet company
* Blaire Reinhard Band, a New Jersey rock band
* [[BRB Internacional]], a Spanish animation studio.
* [[Brienz Rothorn Bahn]], a Swiss railway
* [[Brigade de répression du banditisme]], a special police unit of the French
  Ministry of the Interior.
* British Railways Board, the former governing body of British Railways **BRB
  (Residuary) Ltd., its successor
* BRB, the ISO 3166-1 3-letter country code for Barbados
* BRB, the car number plate for Brandenburg an der Havel
* The blood-retinal barrier, cells in the eye that prevent certain substances
  from entering the tissue of the retina
